              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "the number  of outgoing neutrons was corrected for:",
                " (a) the  probability  of  escape  of  recoil  proton",
                "     tracks from the emulsion;",
                " (b) the  variation  of  the  n-p  scattering   cross",
                "     section with neutron energy;",
                " (c) the background (the relation of  the  background",
                "     to the effect was equal to 22%)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " An  uncertainty of neutron number includes",
                " a statistical error of  correction  for  probability",
                " that  proton  tracks end outside the emulsion and an",
                " uncertainty in determination of the  n-p  scattering",
                " cross section."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The dependence  of  track  length  on  recoil  proton",
                " energy was obtained for NIKFI JA-2 emulsion."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The energy and angular distributions of photoneutrons",
                " from   In-115  are  obtained  at  28  MeV  end-point",
                " bremsstrahlung energy. The contribution of resonance",
                " photoeffect  came  out to 45%  with 10%  error. The",
                " angular distribution of photoneutrons in  the  range",
                " 1.0-11.0 MeV is anisotropic."
              ]
            }
          ],
